{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018WTT5A9jcug74nkvq3gN1W","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 16.1: Hierarchical Flow Schema & Parser\n2\t\n3\tStatus: verifying\n4\t\n5\t## Story\n6\t\n7\tAs a user,\n8\tI want to define `execution`, `story_flow`, and `epic_flow` sections in workflow YAML,\n9\tso that I can configure sprint-level, epic-level, and story-level behavior separately.\n10\t\n11\t## Acceptance Criteria\n12\t\n13\t1. **Given** `src/schemas/workflow.schema.json`, **when** updated, **then** it defines an `execution` object with properties: `max_parallel` (integer, default 1), `isolation` (enum: `worktree`|`none`, default `none`), `merge_strategy` (enum: `rebase`|`merge-commit`, default `merge-commit`), `epic_strategy` (enum: `parallel`|`sequential`, default `sequential`), `story_strategy` (enum: `sequential`|`parallel`, default `sequential`). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n14\t\n15\t2. **Given** the updated schema, **when** a workflow YAML contains a `story_flow` array, **then** it accepts the same format as the existing `flow` field (task ref strings and `{ loop: [...] }` blocks). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n16\t\n17\t3. **Given** the updated schema, **when** a workflow YAML contains an `epic_flow` array, **then** it accepts task ref strings including the built-in names `merge` and `validate` (which do not need to be defined in `tasks:`). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n18\t\n19\t4. **Given** an existing workflow YAML with only `flow:` (no `story_flow`, no `epic_flow`, no `execution`), **when** parsed, **then** it produces identical behavior to the current parser -- `flow` is treated as `story_flow`, and default `execution` values are applied (`max_parallel: 1`, `epic_strategy: sequential`). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n20\t\n21\t5. **Given** `src/lib/hierarchical-flow.ts` is created, **when** `resolveHierarchicalFlow(parsed)` is called with a raw parsed YAML object, **then** it returns a `HierarchicalFlow` containing `execution`, `storyFlow`, `epicFlow`, and `tasks` -- normalizing flat `flow:` into `storyFlow` when no `story_flow` is present. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n22\t\n23\t6. **Given** `workflow-parser.ts`, **when** parsing a workflow with hierarchical sections, **then** it delegates to `hierarchical-flow.ts` for resolution and the returned `ResolvedWorkflow` exposes the hierarchical structure (execution config, story_flow, epic_flow) alongside existing fields. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n24\t\n25\t7. **Given** a `story_flow` that references a task name not defined in `tasks:`, **when** validated, **then** the parser rejects it with a `WorkflowParseError` listing the dangling reference. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n26\t\n27\t8. **Given** an `epic_flow` that references a task name that is neither defined in `tasks:` nor a built-in name (`merge`, `validate`), **when** validated, **then** the parser rejects it with a `WorkflowParseError`. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n28\t\n29\t9. **Given** a workflow with both `flow:` and `story_flow:`, **when** parsed, **then** the parser rejects it with a `WorkflowParseError` explaining that both cannot coexist. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n30\t\n31\t10. **Given** the `task` definition in the schema, **when** a task has `agent: null`, **then** the schema accepts it (agent field allows `null` in addition to string). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n32\t\n33\t11. **Given** the `task` definition in the schema, **when** a task has `scope: per-epic`, **then** the schema accepts it (scope enum extended to include `per-epic`). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n34\t\n35\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n36\t\n37\t- [x] Task 1: Extend `workflow.schema.json` (AC: #1, #2, #3, #10, #11)\n38\t  - [x] Add `execution` object definition with all five properties plus defaults\n39\t  - [x] Add `story_flow` array definition (same shape as current `flow`)\n40\t  - [x] Add `epic_flow` array definition (same shape, but allows built-in refs)\n41\t  - [x] Change `required` from `[\"tasks\", \"flow\"]` to allow either `flow` or `story_flow`\n42\t  - [x] Allow `agent` field in task definition to accept `null` (oneOf: string | null)\n43\t  - [x] Extend `scope` enum to include `per-epic`\n44\t  - [x] Remove top-level `additionalProperties: false` or add new top-level keys\n45\t\n46\t- [x] Task 2: Create `src/lib/hierarchical-flow.ts` (AC: #5, #9)\n47\t  - [x] Define `HierarchicalFlow` interface: `{ execution: ExecutionConfig, storyFlow: FlowStep[], epicFlow: FlowStep[], tasks: Record<string, ResolvedTask> }`\n48\t  - [x] Define `ExecutionConfig` interface with all five fields plus defaults\n49\t  - [x] Implement `resolveHierarchicalFlow(parsed)` function\n50\t  - [x] Handle normalization: if `flow` present and no `story_flow`, copy `flow` to `storyFlow`\n51\t  - [x] Reject if both `flow` and `story_flow` are present\n52\t  - [x] Apply execution defaults when `execution` section is absent\n53\t\n54\t- [x] Task 3: Integrate into `workflow-parser.ts` (AC: #6, #7, #8)\n55\t  - [x] Import and call `resolveHierarchicalFlow` in `validateAndResolve`\n56\t  - [x] Extend `ResolvedWorkflow` interface to include `execution`, `storyFlow`, `epicFlow` fields\n57\t  - [x] Validate `story_flow` task references against `tasks:` section (same as current flow validation)\n58\t  - [x] Validate `epic_flow` task references: check against `tasks:` plus built-in set `{ merge, validate }`\n59\t  - [x] Maintain backward compat: `flow` field still populated for consumers that use it\n60\t\n61\t- [x] Task 4: Update `schema-validate.ts` if needed (AC: #1)\n62\t  - [x] Verify Ajv compiles the updated schema without errors\n63\t  - [x] Ensure `additionalProperties` rules don't block new top-level keys\n64\t\n65\t- [x] Task 5: Write unit tests (AC: #1-#11)\n66\t  - [x] Test: valid workflow with `execution` + `story_flow` + `epic_flow` parses successfully\n67\t  - [x] Test: valid workflow with only `flow:` still parses (backward compat)\n68\t  - [x] Test: `flow:` + `story_flow:` coexistence rejected\n69\t  - [x] Test: `story_flow` referencing undefined task rejected\n70\t  - [x] Test: `epic_flow` referencing undefined non-built-in task rejected\n71\t  - [x] Test: `epic_flow` with built-in `merge` and `validate` accepted\n72\t  - [x] Test: `agent: null` accepted in task definition\n73\t  - [x] Test: `scope: per-epic` accepted in task definition\n74\t  - [x] Test: default execution values applied when `execution` section absent\n75\t  - [x] Test: `resolveHierarchicalFlow` normalizes `flow` to `storyFlow`\n76\t\n77\t## Dev Notes\n78\t\n79\t### Architecture Constraints\n80\t\n81\t- **New file:** `src/lib/hierarchical-flow.ts` -- pure parsing/normalization logic, no side effects.\n82\t- **Modified files:** `src/schemas/workflow.schema.json`, `src/lib/workflow-parser.ts`, possibly `src/lib/schema-validate.ts`.\n83\t- **Pattern to follow:** The existing `workflow-parser.ts` uses `validateAndResolve()` as the central validation+resolution pipeline. The hierarchical flow resolver should integrate there, not bypass it.\n84\t- **JSON Schema approach:** Use `oneOf` at the top level to allow either `{ tasks, flow }` (legacy) or `{ tasks, story_flow, ... }` (hierarchical). Alternatively, make both `flow` and `story_flow` optional and enforce mutual exclusivity in code.\n85\t- **Ajv version:** The project uses `ajv` for JSON Schema draft-07 validation. Ensure the updated schema remains draft-07 compatible.\n86\t\n87\t### Key Interfaces to Define\n88\t\n89\t```typescript\n90\t// In hierarchical-flow.ts\n91\texport interface ExecutionConfig {\n92\t  max_parallel: number;       // default: 1\n93\t  isolation: 'worktree' | 'none';  // default: 'none'\n94\t  merge_strategy: 'rebase' | 'merge-commit';  // default: 'merge-commit'\n95\t  epic_strategy: 'parallel' | 'sequential';   // default: 'sequential'\n96\t  story_strategy: 'sequential' | 'parallel';  // default: 'sequential'\n97\t}\n98\t\n99\texport interface HierarchicalFlow {\n100\t  execution: ExecutionConfig;\n101\t  storyFlow: FlowStep[];\n102\t  epicFlow: FlowStep[];\n103\t  tasks: Record<string, ResolvedTask>;\n104\t}\n105\t```\n106\t\n107\t### Schema Change Details\n108\t\n109\tThe current schema has `\"required\": [\"tasks\", \"flow\"]` and `\"additionalProperties\": false`. Both must change:\n110\t- `required` becomes `[\"tasks\"]` -- either `flow` or `story_flow` must be present (enforced in code or via `oneOf`)\n111\t- `additionalProperties` must allow `execution`, `story_flow`, `epic_flow`\n112\t- The `agent` property in the task definition currently requires `type: \"string\"`. It needs to become `oneOf: [{ type: \"string\" }, { type: \"null\" }]` to support `agent: null`.\n113\t- The `scope` enum `[\"per-story\", \"per-run\"]` must be extended to `[\"per-story\", \"per-run\", \"per-epic\"]`.\n114\t\n115\t### Built-in Epic Flow Tasks\n116\t\n117\t`merge` and `validate` are engine-handled built-in names that do NOT need entries in `tasks:`. The `epic_flow` validation must whitelist these names when checking referential integrity. The whitelist should be a constant (e.g., `BUILTIN_EPIC_FLOW_TASKS = new Set(['merge', 'validate'])`) for extensibility.\n118\t\n119\t### Backward Compatibility\n120\t\n121\tThis is the most critical constraint. Existing workflows that look like:\n122\t\n123\t```yaml\n124\ttasks:\n125\t  implement: { agent: dev }\n126\t  verify: { agent: evaluator, scope: per-run }\n127\tflow:\n128\t  - implement\n129\t  - verify\n130\t```\n131\t\n132\tMust parse identically to today. The resolved `storyFlow` should equal what `flow` currently produces. The `execution` config should be all defaults. No `epicFlow` is generated.\n133\t\n134\t### Referential Integrity\n135\t\n136\tThe existing `validateAndResolve()` already validates `flow` task references. The new code must:\n137\t1. Apply the same validation to `story_flow` task references\n138\t2. Apply similar validation to `epic_flow` but with the built-in whitelist\n139\t3. Not double-validate when `flow` is normalized to `storyFlow`\n140\t\n141\t### Project Structure Notes\n142\t\n143\t- Source files: TypeScript in `src/lib/`, compiled to `dist/`\n144\t- Tests: `src/lib/__tests__/*.test.ts` (vitest)\n145\t- Schemas: `src/schemas/*.schema.json`\n146\t- The module uses ESM (`import.meta.url`, `.js` extensions in imports)\n147\t- Test runner: vitest for `.test.ts`, BATS for `.bats` integration tests\n148\t\n149\t### References\n150\t\n151\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-parallel-execution.md#Epic 16, Story 16.1]\n152\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-parallel-execution.md#Decision 4]\n153\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-parallel-execution.md#Decision 5]\n154\t- [Source: src/schemas/workflow.schema.json — current schema, entire file]\n155\t- [Source: src/lib/workflow-parser.ts — current parser with validateAndResolve()]\n156\t- [Source: src/lib/schema-validate.ts — Ajv setup]\n157\t\n158\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n159\t## Verification Requirements\n160\t\n161\t- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/16-1-hierarchical-flow-schema-parser-proof.md)\n162\t- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n163\t- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n164\t\n165\t## Documentation Requirements\n166\t\n167\t- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n168\t- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/16-1-hierarchical-flow-schema-parser.md\n169\t\n170\t## Testing Requirements\n171\t\n172\t- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n173\t- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n174\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n175\t\n176\t## Dev Agent Record\n177\t\n178\t### Agent Model Used\n179\t\n180\tClaude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n181\t\n182\t### Debug Log References\n183\t\n184\tN/A\n185\t\n186\t### Completion Notes List\n187\t\n188\t- Task 1: Extended `workflow.schema.json` — extracted `flowArray` definition for reuse by `flow`, `story_flow`, and `epic_flow`. Added `execution` object definition with 5 properties. Changed `agent` to `oneOf: [string, null]`. Extended `scope` enum with `per-epic`. Changed `required` from `[\"tasks\", \"flow\"]` to `[\"tasks\"]` (mutual exclusivity enforced in parser).\n189\t- Task 2: Created `src/lib/hierarchical-flow.ts` with `ExecutionConfig`, `HierarchicalFlow` interfaces, `BUILTIN_EPIC_FLOW_TASKS` constant, `EXECUTION_DEFAULTS`, and `resolveHierarchicalFlow()` function. Pure normalization logic, no side effects.\n190\t- Task 3: Integrated hierarchical flow into `workflow-parser.ts`. Extended `ResolvedWorkflow` with `execution`, `storyFlow`, `epicFlow`. Added `validateFlowReferences()` helper for flow-to-task referential integrity with built-in whitelist support. Updated `validateAndResolve()` to handle both legacy and hierarchical workflows. Maintained full backward compat — `flow` field is always populated.\n191\t- Task 4: Schema compiles without errors under Ajv draft-07. `additionalProperties` still blocks unknown top-level keys. Added `execution`, `story_flow`, `epic_flow` as allowed properties.\n192\t- Task 5: Wrote 28 unit tests covering all 11 acceptance criteria. Updated 3 existing test files (`driver-health-check.test.ts`, `workflow-engine.test.ts`, `schema-validate.test.ts`) for compatibility with new `ResolvedWorkflow` interface. All 4676 tests pass (1 pre-existing failure in `stats.test.ts` unrelated to changes).\n193\t- Also fixed `src/commands/run.ts` to handle `agent: null` tasks (skip agent resolution for engine-handled tasks).\n194\t\n195\t### Change Log\n196\t\n197\t- 2026-04-03: Implemented story 16.1 — hierarchical flow schema & parser\n198\t\n199\t### File List\n200\t\n201\t- src/schemas/workflow.schema.json (modified)\n202\t- src/lib/hierarchical-flow.ts (new)\n203\t- src/lib/workflow-parser.ts (modified)\n204\t- src/commands/run.ts (modified)\n205\t- src/lib/__tests__/hierarchical-flow.test.ts (new)\n206\t- src/lib/__tests__/driver-health-check.test.ts (modified)\n207\t- src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts (modified)\n208\t- src/lib/__tests__/schema-validate.test.ts (modified)\n209\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01P6VJWwxyDkdUjYM8CN6t2V","session_id":"8a461711-53e2-475a-88dd-c7013f6080c5","uuid":"72d81779-8681-48a3-bb2e-cc4a48b573ff","timestamp":"2026-04-03T17:08:05.491Z"}
