{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01BkTmkemoN7u3LKK2ZmCnij","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_012cBsy4xcDvaJk5JYzmcgA6","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/16-2-engine-handled-null-tasks.md","old_string":"- [ ] Task 1: Create null task handler registry (AC: #2, #5)\n  - [ ] Create `src/lib/null-task-registry.ts`\n  - [ ] Define `TaskContext` interface: `{ storyKey, taskName, cost, durationMs, outputContract, projectDir }`\n  - [ ] Define `NullTaskHandler` type: `(ctx: TaskContext) => Promise<NullTaskResult>`\n  - [ ] Define `NullTaskResult` interface: `{ success: boolean, output?: string }`\n  - [ ] Implement `registerNullTask(name, handler)` function\n  - [ ] Implement `getNullTask(name)` function returning handler or undefined\n  - [ ] Implement `listNullTasks()` returning all registered names (for error messages)\n  - [ ] Register a no-op `telemetry` handler as placeholder (real implementation in story 16-3)\n\n- [ ] Task 2: Add null task dispatch path in workflow engine (AC: #1, #4, #7, #8)\n  - [ ] In `dispatchTaskWithResult` (or a new sibling function), detect `task.agent === null`\n  - [ ] When null: look up handler via `getNullTask(taskName)`\n  - [ ] If handler found: build `TaskContext`, call handler, build `OutputContract` from result\n  - [ ] If handler not found: throw error with code `NULL_TASK_NOT_FOUND`\n  - [ ] Write `TaskCheckpoint` to state after handler completes (same as agent dispatch)\n  - [ ] Ensure `previousOutputContract` chain works across null→agent and agent→null transitions\n  - [ ] Per-story scope: iterate work items and call handler per item (same as agent dispatch)\n  - [ ] Per-run scope: call handler once with sentinel key (same as agent dispatch)\n  - [ ] Crash recovery: skip null tasks that have completed checkpoints (same logic)\n\n- [ ] Task 3: Update `run.ts` agent resolution to skip null agents (AC: #1)\n  - [ ] Verify the existing `if (task.agent != null)` guard in `run.ts` line 141 correctly skips null agents\n  - [ ] If already correct (from 16-1), no changes needed — just verify with a test\n\n- [ ] Task 4: Write unit tests (AC: #1-#8)\n  - [ ] Test: null task registry register/get/list\n  - [ ] Test: unknown null task returns undefined from registry, engine throws `NULL_TASK_NOT_FOUND`\n  - [ ] Test: engine skips driver dispatch for `agent: null` tasks\n  - [ ] Test: null task handler receives correct `TaskContext`\n  - [ ] Test: `TaskCheckpoint` written after null task completion\n  - [ ] Test: `OutputContract` produced by null task has `driver: \"engine\"`, `cost_usd: 0`\n  - [ ] Test: mixed flow with null + agent tasks executes in order\n  - [ ] Test: crash recovery skips completed null tasks\n  - [ ] Test: null task completes in <10ms (performance assertion)\n  - [ ] Test: per-story null task iterates all work items\n  - [ ] Test: per-run null task runs once with sentinel key","new_string":"- [x] Task 1: Create null task handler registry (AC: #2, #5)\n  - [x] Create `src/lib/null-task-registry.ts`\n  - [x] Define `TaskContext` interface: `{ storyKey, taskName, cost, durationMs, outputContract, projectDir }`\n  - [x] Define `NullTaskHandler` type: `(ctx: TaskContext) => Promise<NullTaskResult>`\n  - [x] Define `NullTaskResult` interface: `{ success: boolean, output?: string }`\n  - [x] Implement `registerNullTask(name, handler)` function\n  - [x] Implement `getNullTask(name)` function returning handler or undefined\n  - [x] Implement `listNullTasks()` returning all registered names (for error messages)\n  - [x] Register a no-op `telemetry` handler as placeholder (real implementation in story 16-3)\n\n- [x] Task 2: Add null task dispatch path in workflow engine (AC: #1, #4, #7, #8)\n  - [x] In `dispatchTaskWithResult` (or a new sibling function), detect `task.agent === null`\n  - [x] When null: look up handle