{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01E368mBox6AGS9E4aPFSS48","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is the summary of what was done.\n\n**Story 16-2: Engine-Handled Null Tasks — Implementation Complete**\n\n**Files created:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/null-task-registry.ts` — Registry with `registerNullTask()`, `getNullTask()`, `listNullTasks()`, interfaces (`TaskContext`, `NullTaskResult`, `NullTaskHandler`), and built-in no-op telemetry handler\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/null-task-registry.test.ts` — 8 unit tests\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/null-task-engine.test.ts` — 13 integration tests\n\n**Files modified:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` — Added `executeNullTask()` helper, null task branches in both `executeWorkflow()` (per-run + per-story) and `executeLoopBlock()`, `checkDriverHealth()` skip for null agents, `isEngineError()` type guard\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/16-2-engine-handled-null-tasks.md` — Status set to `review`, all tasks checked off\n\n**Test results:** 4712 passed, 1 pre-existing failure (stats.test.ts, unrelated). All 21 new tests pass. All 138 existing workflow-engine tests pass.\n\n**Task 3 verification:** `run.ts` line 141 already has `if (task.agent != null)` guard from story 16-1 — no changes needed.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Workaround:** The `executeNullTask` throws a plain `EngineError` object (not an Error subclass) for `NULL_TASK_NOT_FOUND`. Added `isEngineError()` type guard to handle this in catch blocks. This works but is slightly inconsistent with `DispatchError` which extends `Error`. Story 16-3 or a future cleanup should consider making `EngineError` a proper Error subclass.\n- **Code quality concern:** The null task branches in `executeWorkflow()` and `executeLoopBlock()` duplicate scope-handling logic (per-run vs per-story). This is the same pattern the agent path uses, but it adds more code duplication. A refactor to extract a generic \"execute task for scope\" function could reduce this.\n- **Edge case:** The `cost` field in `TaskContext` only carries forward the previous task's `cost_usd`, not the accumulated total across all tasks. The story spec says \"total cost so far from previous tasks\" but the engine doesn't currently track cumulative cost. The implementation uses `previousOutputContract?.cost_usd ?? 0` which is the single previous task's cost. This matches how the engine works today but may need revisiting.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 25\n- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 11, Edit: 7, Grep: 3, Write: 3, Glob: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npx tsc --noEmit` (~40 lines), `npx vitest run` full suite (~30 lines), `npx vitest run` null task tests (~25 lines)\n- Files read: 10 unique, 14 total reads (workflow-engine.ts read 5 times due to size limits)\n- Redundant operations: None significant. The 5 reads of workflow-engine.ts were necessary due to the 10k token limit requiring offset-based reading of a 1116-line file."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a01847a97803bab00 (use SendMessage with to: 'a01847a97803bab00' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 75221\ntool_uses: 44\nduration_ms: 386777</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8a461711-53e2-475a-88dd-c7013f6080c5","uuid":"8fbdb6ef-bf20-458b-a0ec-7857afa873ec","timestamp":"2026-04-03T17:19:13.267Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-dev-story for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/16-2-engine-handled-null-tasks.md — implement all tasks, write tests, and mark the story for review. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously through all tasks until complete. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Sessi